On October 30th, the First Lady, Melania Trump, and the Second Lady, Karen Pence, will visit Charleston, South Carolina. They will be highlighting the emergency preparedness efforts within the community. The two will visit Lambs Elementary School to participate in the Red Cross's Pillowcase Project, which is an emergency response program for children to help them be better prepared for natural disasters. They will also visit Joint Base Charleston to meet with military personnel and civilians, thanking them for their service and learning more about the base's capabilities in disaster response and recovery. Mrs. Trump will deliver remarks to the troops and families to express gratitude for their service and sacrifices.